26/05/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Federal Foreign Minister Goran Svilanovic said Sunday (25 May) the US administration had asked Belgrade to sign a reciprocal treaty barring extraditions to the International Criminal Court.
Svilanovic said there is no pressure to resolve the issue quickly, adding that the government would address the request in a few weeks.
EU authorities have urged Balkan countries not to sign the document.
In other news Sunday, Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic said he views relations with Montenegro as good, and that he does not foresee problems within the new federation.
According to Zivkovic, both Belgrade and Podgorica have the political will to complete the integration process.
(B92, BBC, Tanjug, Vijesti - 25/05/03)
